doc.after: The Australian National Botanic Gardens ANBG are located in Canberra and are administered by the Australian Government s Department of the Environment and Heritage The botanic gardens are a collection of native Australian flora the mission of the ANBG is to study and promote Australia s flora The gardens maintains a wide variety of botanical resources for researchers and cultivates native plants threatened in the wild
